space.arim.api.util.collect

Class CalculationMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • space.arim.api.util.collect.FunctionalMap<K,V>
      • space.arim.api.util.collect.CalculationMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type
    V - the value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>, UnmodifiableByDefaultMap<K,V>

    public class CalculationMap<K,V>
extends FunctionalMap<K,V>
    A map which takes from a fixed key set and maps them dynamically (i.e., calculates) to a value when FunctionalMap.get(Object) is called.

    Principles:
    1 There is a set of keys considered valid key objects.
    2 The mapped values are computed at call time.
    3 An entry is contained within the map if the entry key maps to the entry value.
    4 The map is unmodifiable.

    The specifications follow from the principles.
    Specifications:
    * keySet() returns the key set provided at construction. (principle 1)
    * size() and isEmpty() redirect to the key set's equivalents. (principle 1)
    * containsKey(Object) returns true if and only if the key object is contained in the key set according to Set.contains(Object). (principle 1)
    * FunctionalMap.values() returns a collection which dynamically reflects the state of this map (See CalculationMapValues for more information). containsValue(Object) returns true if and only if the object is contained within this collection. (principle 2)
    * FunctionalMap.entrySet() returns a set which dynamically reflects the state of this map (See CalculationMapEntrySet for more information). (principles 2 and 3)
    * The map's modification methods all throw UnsupportedOperationException. (principle 4)
    Author:
    A248
